You are helping me build GlobalTradeX, a full-stack web platform for
international trade management. Here is everything you need to know.
--- WHAT IS IT ---
GlobalTradeX is a B2B SaaS platform that digitalizes and automates the
import/export workflow for businesses in international trade.
It connects five user types on one platform: importers, exporters,
freight forwarders, customs brokers, and a platform admin.
It replaces manual paperwork, email chains, and spreadsheets with a
unified digital workspace. Each role has its own dashboard and sees
only the data relevant to their job.
--- THE 5 USER ROLES ---
1. Importer: Buys goods from abroad. Creates shipments, tracks delivery,
uploads payment documents, calculates import duties.
2. Exporter: Sells goods abroad. Manages product catalog with HS codes,
creates outgoing shipments, uploads commercial invoices.
3. Freight Forwarder (Transitaire): The logistics agent. Updates shipment
statuses in real time as cargo moves through ports and customs.
4. Customs Broker (Courtier en Douane): The compliance specialist.
Reviews documents, verifies completeness, uses AI to detect missing fields.
5. Admin: Manages all user accounts, assigns roles, monitors all shipments,
and views global analytics across the entire platform.
--- CORE FEATURES ---
- Shipment lifecycle: pending > in_transit > customs_hold > delivered
- Document management: upload, store, and verify trade documents
- AI document verification: OpenAI Vision detects missing fields
- AI route optimizer: GPT-4o suggests 3 optimized shipping routes
- AI chatbot: floating chat widget with role-aware context
- AI talking avatar: D-ID video avatar with cloned voice (ElevenLabs)
and voice input via OpenAI Whisper
- Duty and freight calculator: estimates taxes by HS code and freight cost
- Real-time notifications: in-app, email (SMTP), and SMS (Twilio)
- Role-based access control: JWT + require_role() + RoleGuard component
- Analytics: KPI cards and Chart.js charts per role
--- PROJECT CONTEXT ---
This is a Bachelor graduation project (Projet de Fin d'Etudes) in Tunisia.
Goal: working features, clean code, easy to explain to a jury.
Always generate code I can understand and present with confidence.
Medium complexity — avoid over-engineering.
How to use: Paste this once at the start of every new Cursor session
Here is the full technical setup. Always follow these conventions.
--- TECH STACK ---
Frontend : Next.js 14, App Router, plain .jsx (no TypeScript)
Styling : Tailwind CSS only — no custom CSS files
Charts : Chart.js + react-chartjs-2
HTTP : Axios — configured instance at frontend/lib/api.js
Auth state: React Context at frontend/context/AuthContext.jsx
Cookies : js-cookie — JWT stored as cookie named 'token'
Icons : lucide-react
Toasts : react-hot-toast
Backend : Python FastAPI 0.111+
ORM : SQLAlchemy 2.0 with declarative_base()
DB driver: PyMySQL — connection: mysql+pymysql://root:@localhost:3306/globaltradex
Database : MySQL 8 via XAMPP on localhost:3306, database name: globaltradex
Auth : JWT via python-jose, passwords hashed with passlib/bcrypt
Validation: Pydantic v2 schemas in backend/schemas/
Uploads : FastAPI UploadFile — files saved in backend/uploads/
AI : OpenAI Python SDK — model: gpt-4o for all AI features
Avatar : D-ID REST API (POST https://api.d-id.com/talks)
Voice : ElevenLabs API + OpenAI Whisper for speech-to-text
Email : smtplib with Gmail SMTP
SMS : Twilio Python SDK
--- FOLDER STRUCTURE ---
globaltradex/
