RoleGuard.jsx, Chatbot.jsx, AvatarModal.jsx
context/AuthContext.jsx
lib/api.js
middleware.js
.env.local <- NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
--- KEY CONVENTIONS ---
- All FastAPI routes use prefix /api (e.g. /api/shipments)
- All protected routes: Depends(get_current_user) from auth/dependencies.py
- Role checks: Depends(require_role(['rolename'])) — HTTP 403 if blocked
- DB sessions: always db = Depends(get_db) — never create sessions manually
- Next.js data-fetching pages: always add 'use client' at the top
- Always use api from '@/lib/api' for calls — never raw fetch()
- Always read user from useAuth() hook — never read cookie directly
- Status colors: pending=orange, in_transit=blue, delivered=green,
delayed=red, customs_hold=purple, cancelled=gray
- All forms: loading spinner on submit, react-hot-toast on success/error
Database name: globaltradex — MySQL 8 via XAMPP on localhost:3306.
Root user, no password (XAMPP default).
SQLAlchemy connection string: mysql+pymysql://root:@localhost:3306/globaltradex
TABLE: users
id INT PK AUTO_INCREMENT
full_name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL
email VARCHAR(150) UNIQUE NOT NULL INDEX
password_hash VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
role ENUM('admin','importateur','exportateur','transitaire','courtier')
phone VARCHAR(20) nullable
is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE
created_at DATETIME DEFAULT NOW()
TABLE: products
id INT PK AUTO_INCREMENT
user_id INT FK -> users.id CASCADE DELETE
name VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL
hs_code VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL
description TEXT nullable
unit_price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL
quantity INT DEFAULT 0
unit VARCHAR(20) DEFAULT 'pcs'
origin_country VARCHAR(100) nullable
created_at DATETIME DEFAULT NOW()
TABLE: shipments
id INT PK AUTO_INCREMENT
owner_id INT FK -> users.id CASCADE DELETE
reference VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE format: GTX-YYYYMMDD-XXXXX
origin VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL
destination VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL
cargo_type ENUM('general','fragile','dangerous','perishable','oversized')
transport_mode ENUM('air','sea','road','rail')
status ENUM('pending','in_transit','customs_hold','delivered',
'delayed','cancelled') DEFAULT 'pending'
weight_kg DECIMAL(10,2) nullable
volume_m3 DECIMAL(10,3) nullable
estimated_value DECIMAL(15,2) nullable
currency VARCHAR(10) DEFAULT 'USD'
departure_date DATE nullable
arrival_date DATE nullable
notes TEXT nullable
created_at DATETIME DEFAULT NOW()
updated_at DATETIME ON UPDATE NOW()
TABLE: documents
id INT PK AUTO_INCREMENT
shipment_id INT FK -> shipments.id CASCADE DELETE
uploaded_by INT FK -> users.id
filename VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL UUID-based filename on disk
original_name VARCHAR(255) original filename shown to user
file_type ENUM('invoice','certificate','bill_of_lading',
'customs_declaration','packing_list','other')
file_size INT nullable
file_path VARCHAR(500) path inside uploads/
is_verified BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
ai_result JSON nullable OpenAI verification result
uploaded_at DATETIME DEFAULT NOW()
TABLE: notifications
id INT PK AUTO_INCREMENT
user_id INT FK -> users.id CASCADE DELETE
title VARCHAR(200) NOT NULL
message TEXT NOT NULL
type ENUM('info','success','warning','error') DEFAULT 'info'
is_read BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE
shipment_id INT FK -> shipments.id ON DELETE SET NULL nullable
created_at DATETIME DEFAULT NOW()
TABLE: shipment_products (many-to-many join)
id INT PK AUTO_INCREMENT
shipment_id INT FK -> shipments.id CASCADE DELETE
product_id INT FK -> products.id CASCADE DELETE
quantity INT DEFAULT 1
unit_price DECIMAL(10,2) nullable
RELATIONSHIPS:
users (1) ---> (N) products via user_id
users (1) ---> (N) shipments via owner_id
users (1) ---> (N) notifications via user_id
shipments (1) -> (N) documents via shipment_id
shipments (N) <-> (N) products via shipment_products join table
shipments (1) -> (N) notifications via shipment_id
Use these exact column names and types in all SQLAlchemy models and Pydantic schemas.
GlobalTradeX uses a professional blue-themed design. Always follow these rules.
--- GLOBAL COLORS (Tailwind classes) ---
Page background : bg-gray-50 (or bg-slate-50)
Primary action : bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white
Card background : bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl
Sidebar : bg-slate-900 text-white (dark sidebar)
Header : bg-white border-b border-gray-200 shadow-sm
--- ROLE ACCENT COLORS ---
Admin : bg-purple-50 border-purple-500 text-purple-800
Importer : bg-blue-50 border-blue-500 text-blue-800
Exporter : bg-green-50 border-green-500 text-green-800
Freight Forwarder: bg-amber-50 border-amber-500 text-amber-800
Customs Broker : bg-pink-50 border-pink-500 text-pink-800
--- STATUS BADGE CLASSES ---
pending : bg-orange-100 text-orange-700 border border-orange-300
in_transit : bg-blue-100 text-blue-700 border border-blue-300
customs_hold : bg-purple-100 text-purple-700 border border-purple-300
delivered : bg-green-100 text-green-700 border border-green-300
delayed : bg-red-100 text-red-700 border border-red-300
cancelled : bg-gray-100 text-gray-500 border border-gray-300
All badges : text-xs font-medium px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded-full
--- LAYOUT STRUCTURE ---
Sidebar width : w-64 (256px), fixed, h-screen, bg-slate-900
Main content : ml-64 min-h-screen bg-gray-50
Page padding : p-6 or p-8
Header : fixed top-0 left-64 right-0 h-16 bg-white z-10
Content with hdr : pt-16 (offset below fixed header)
--- COMPONENT PATTERNS ---
KPI card : bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-5
small icon box top-left (role accent color)
muted label text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1
large value text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900
Table : bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden
thead: bg-gray-50 text-xs uppercase text-gray-500 tracking-wider
th/td: px-6 py-3
tbody rows: divide-y divide-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50 transition
Form card : bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto
Input : w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-lg text-sm
focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500
Label : block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1
Error text : text-sm text-red-600 mt-1
--- BUTTONS ---
Primary : bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg
text-sm font-medium transition-colors disabled:opacity-50
Secondary : bg-white border border-gray-300 hover:bg-gray-50 text-gray-700
px-4 py-2 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium
Danger : bg-red-600 hover:bg-red-700 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-lg
--- SIDEBAR NAV LINKS ---
Inactive: flex items-center gap-3 px-3 py-2 rounded-lg text-gray-300
hover:bg-white/10 hover:text-white transition text-sm
Active : flex items-center gap-3 px-3 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600
text-white text-sm font-medium
--- LOADING AND EMPTY STATES ---
Page spinner : flex items-center justify-center h-64
animate-spin h-8 w-8 border-4 border-blue-600
border-t-transparent rounded-full
Skeleton row : animate-pulse bg-gray-200 rounded h-4 w-full
Empty state : text-center py-12 text-gray-400 text-sm
with a relevant lucide-react icon above the message
--- RESPONSIVE ---
Breakpoints : sm(640) md(768) lg(1024) xl(1280)
KPI grid : grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 xl:grid-cols-4 gap-4
Sidebar : hidden lg:flex on mobile, hamburger toggle
Tables : overflow-x-auto wrapper on mobile
Never hardcode hex colors. Always use Tailwind color classes.
Never use inline style= for colors unless no Tailwind equivalent exists.
Here is every feature in GlobalTradeX and how each one works.
=== AUTHENTICATION ===
POST /api/auth/register create account (full_name, email, password, role)
POST /api/auth/login verify credentials, return JWT + user object
GET /api/users/me return current user profile
PUT /api/users/me update own profile
JWT stored in cookie 'token', sent as Authorization: Bearer
Token expiry: 1440 minutes (24 hours)
=== SHIPMENT MANAGEMENT ===
POST /api/shipments importateur + admin can create
GET /api/shipments importateur sees own / admin sees all
query params: status, page, limit
GET /api/shipments/{id} owner or admin only
PATCH /api/shipments/{id}/status transitaire + admin only
DELETE /api/shipments/{id} admin only
Reference format: GTX-YYYYMMDD-XXXXX (auto-generated on creation)
Valid status transitions:
pending -> in_transit allowed
in_transit -> customs_hold allowed
in_transit -> delivered allowed
in_transit -> delayed allowed
customs_hold -> in_transit allowed
customs_hold -> delivered allowed
delayed -> in_transit allowed
delivered -> anything NOT ALLOWED (raise HTTP 400)
=== PRODUCT CATALOG ===
POST /api/products exportateur + admin
GET /api/products exportateur sees own / admin sees all
PUT /api/products/{id} owner or admin (check ownership, else 403)
DELETE /api/products/{id} owner or admin
=== DOCUMENT MANAGEMENT ===
POST /api/documents/upload all roles, multipart/form-data
saves file to uploads/ with UUID name
GET /api/documents/{shipment_id} all roles with shipment access
DELETE /api/documents/{id} uploader or admin
PATCH /api/documents/{id}/verify courtier + admin
body: {is_verified, rejection_reason}
POST /api/documents/{id}/ai-verify courtier + admin
calls OpenAI Vision, saves to ai_result
ai_result JSON shape: {valid, document_type, missing_fields[], errors[], confidence}
=== CALCULATORS ===
POST /api/calculator/duties
input : hs_code, origin_country, destination_country, declared_value
output: duty_rate_percent, vat_percent, total_tax_usd
POST /api/calculator/freight
input : weight_kg, length_cm, width_cm, height_cm, transport_mode
output: volumetric_weight_kg, billable_weight_kg, cost_usd, eta_days
=== ANALYTICS ===
GET /api/analytics/shipments current user stats (admin = all users)
returns: {total, by_status:{pending,in_transit,...}, by_month:[]}
GET /api/analytics/revenue estimated revenue by month
GET /api/analytics/global admin only — platform-wide numbers
=== NOTIFICATIONS ===
GET /api/notifications newest first, current user
PATCH /api/notifications/{id}/read mark one read
PATCH /api/notifications/read-all mark all read
Auto-created when: shipment created, status changed, document verified/rejected
Email via Gmail SMTP on all events
SMS via Twilio on status: in_transit, delivered, delayed
=== AI FEATURES ===
POST /api/ai/chat
input : {message, history[], user_role, recent_shipments[]}
model : gpt-4o with role-aware system prompt
output: {response: string}
used by: Chatbot.jsx floating widget on all pages
POST /api/ai/suggest-routes
input : {origin, destination, cargo_type, weight_kg, urgency}
model : gpt-4o — returns exactly 3 routes as JSON array
output: {routes:[{carrier,mode,cost_usd,eta_days,risk_level,notes}]}
used by: new shipment form Step 2, calculator page
POST /api/ai/verify-document
input : file (image/PDF), document_type_expected
model : gpt-4o with vision (base64 image)
output: {valid,document_type,missing_fields[],errors[],confidence}
used by: documents page for courtier role
=== AVATAR AI ===
POST /api/avatar/talk
input : {message, user_role, recent_shipments[]}
step 1: GPT-4o generates text response
step 2: text sent to D-ID API (POST https://api.d-id.com/talks)
step 3: poll D-ID until video ready (max 30 seconds)
output: {video_url, text_response}
frontend: AvatarModal.jsx floating button on all dashboard pages
POST /api/avatar/transcribe
input : audio file WAV/MP3 from browser MediaRecorder
uses : OpenAI Whisper API
output: {text, language}
POST /api/avatar/speak
input : {text, voice_id}
uses : ElevenLabs API with user's cloned voice
output: MP3 audio bytes
=== FRONTEND COMPONENTS ===
RoleGuard.jsx wraps pages, blocks wrong roles with 403 UI
Chatbot.jsx floating bubble bottom-right, slide-in panel
AvatarModal.jsx floating button, modal with video + mic input
Sidebar.jsx role-aware nav — different links per role
Header.jsx user name, role badge, notif bell, logout
KPICard.jsx reusable stat card with icon, label, value
DataTable.jsx generic paginated table with column config
StatusBadge.jsx colored pill for shipment status values
FileUpload.jsx drag-and-drop uploader with progress bar
When I ask you to build any feature, use this list to understand
what other parts it connects to and which API endpoints it calls.